{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"fields":{"description":"## What\nPersist a bounded bug-classification enum at close, replacing today's validated-then-discarded free-text `--reason`. Adds a REQUIRED `--class` param to `transition` for bug closes and folds `close_class` into reduced ticket state so it survives and is queryable, with the vocabulary that feeds the classification metrics.\n\n## Files\n- `src/rebar/_commands/transition.py` â€” parse a new `--class <value>` flag in `_parse_flags` (alongside `--reason`).\n- `src/rebar/_commands/txn.py` â€” validate the enum for bug closes (replacing `bug_close_reason_ok` at the transition_core guard, ~line 221-232) and write `close_class` into `status_data`.\n- `src/rebar/_commands/transition_close.py` â€” CRITICAL: the `_completion_precheck` guard at line ~121 also calls `txn.bug_close_reason_ok(reason)`; update it to accept a valid `close_class` (or skip the reason pre-check when `close_class` is supplied). Thread `close_class` through the close path.\n- `src/rebar/reducer/_processors.py` â€” CRITICAL: `process_status` only folds a fixed set of keys; add a `_fold_close_class(state, data)` helper (mirroring `_fold_claimed_session`) that sets `state['close_class'] = data['close_class']` on a `*->closed` edge, called in BOTH the fork-winner and normal-update branches â€” otherwise `close_class` never surfaces into reduced state and `rebar show` cannot see it.\n- `src/rebar/schemas/ticket_state.schema.json` â€” add optional `close_class`.\n- `src/rebar/_cli/help/transition.txt`, `docs/ticket-model.md`, `docs/user-guide.md` â€” document the enum.\n- `tests/interfaces/lifecycle/test_bug_close_class.py` â€” new.\n\n## Approach\nThe bug-close reason is required today but never persisted (`txn.py` validates then drops it), so replacing it with a bounded, folded enum is friction-neutral-to-negative and turns wasted input into a hard signal. `--class` is REQUIRED on bug close (mirrors the old required `--reason`): omitting it exits nonzero with a message listing the allowed values. Because `status_data` keys are not auto-surfaced, the enum only reaches `rebar show` via an explicit `_fold_close_class` fold â€” the exact-parallel of `_fold_claimed_session`. The guard lives at two sites (`txn.py` transition_core AND `transition_close.py` `_completion_precheck`), both updated. Closed MECE vocabulary with an escape + hygiene values: `regression`, `plan_defect`, `env_integration`, `flaky`, `preexisting`, `not_a_bug`, `duplicate`, `escalated`, `undetermined`. `escalated` preserves today's Escalated branch; the rest refine Fixed. Additive/optional schema field (readers tolerate absence); back-out = stop requiring/writing it.\n\n## Tests\n- CLI (real subprocess): closing a bug with `--class regression` persists and surfaces `close_class=regression`; omitting `--class` exits nonzero; an invalid class is rejected; `undetermined` is accepted.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `tests/interfaces/lifecycle/test_bug_close_class.py` passes: `rebar transition <bug> in_progress closed --class regression` exits 0 and `rebar show <bug> --output json | jq -e '.close_class==\\\"regression\\\"'` matches (proving the fold reaches reduced state).\n- [ ] closing a bug with NO `--class` exits nonzero with a message naming the allowed values â€” CLI test asserts exit != 0.\n- [ ] a value outside the enum is rejected with a nonzero exit â€” CLI test asserts exit != 0.\n- [ ] closing with `--class undetermined` succeeds (escape value) â€” CLI test asserts exit 0."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784420463846304001,"uuid":"06b39b33-d4f4-475a-a894-a1ca98dc7429"}